te, advance, and safeguard research at UIC by conducting world-class research that advances the field of knowledge both locally and globally.”  This is accomplished by supporting three distinctive goals:   Research Development  Research Infrastructure  Research Compliance   This site has been created as a resource for our research community in order to provide information needed to conduct clinical research and provide the steps required to utilize services or resources of the University of Illinois Hospital and Clinics, UIC College of Medicine office-based clinics, Mile Square Health Center, or Ryan White Infectious Disease Clinics.  For further information and assistance, please contact researchfinance@uic.edu .          Clinical Research    Back to main content           Research Study Billing Compliance    Getting Your Research Study in Epic    Clinic/Hospital    IRB Application    Externally Sponsored Clinical Trials    Center for Clinical and Translational Science (CCTS) Services    Clinicaltrials.gov    Common Clinical Trial Terms    Forms    Contact                   UIC Logo         Office Of  The Vice  Chancellor  For  Research                   Contact   Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research  1737 West Polk Street, Suite 310, MC 672, Chicago, IL 60612  Phone: (312) 996-4995  Fax: (312 ) 996-9598  ovcrweb@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 